snippet.textDisplay: the Analogue SG is not Sega jumping on the mini console bandwagon, but Analogue expanding beyond their Analogue NT and Super NT, which are FPGA hardware-emulation boxes that run cartridge games for the Sega MegaDrive/Genesis, Nintendo Entertainment System and Super Nintendo respectively. The Analogue consoles are not software emulators with built in games like the NES Classic, SNES Classic, or PlayStation Classic. They are FPGAs (basically CPUs that can be altered after production) that emulate the original hardware as accurately as possible. This means that you can't install multiple games to them. They take the original cartridges instead.
